spans.text: to me shall be no more
from dust by power divine ; Its features change , it's pale , it's cold — Hence dreadful spectre ! to behold Thy aspect
it's cold — Hence dreadful spectre ! to behold Thy aspect
what I am demand the knee , Or look on aught around with scorn
what I am demand the knee , Or look on aught around with scorn
this spark that warms , that guides , That lives , that thinks , what fate betides
this be dust , a kneaded clod
thee must for ever know , Immortal and divine
Trees deeply rooted in the ground
Trees deeply rooted in the ground
To earth , alas ! too firmly bound , Trees deeply rooted in the ground ,
greatness gains , How do you bind with silken chains , Which ask Herculean strength to break
How do you bind with silken chains , Which ask Herculean strength to break
Each blind to fate's approaching hour , Intrigues , or fights , for wealth , or power , And slumbering dangers

the world's victor mount his car
nations bled Beneath his chariot's fervid wheel
to Frenzy's rage , And all the world
